# Memory Extraction Before Summarizing

## Critical: Store Important Info in Memories
Before marking messages as summarized, check if any important information should be stored as memories:

### Lodging Information
- If user selected specific hotel â†’ Store as episodic memory (trip-specific, 90-day TTL)
- If user expressed hotel preference â†’ Store as declarative memory (long-term fact, no TTL)

### Activity Information
- If user visited specific attraction â†’ Store as episodic memory
- If user expressed activity preference â†’ Store as procedural memory (behavioral pattern, no TTL)

### Dining Information
- If user ate at specific restaurant â†’ Store as episodic memory
- If user expressed dietary restriction â†’ Store as declarative memory (CRITICAL - long-term)

### Itinerary Information
- Trip details are already stored via create_new_trip/update_trip (no action needed)
- Reference trip ID in summary for future retrieval

